org.drools.planner.examples.ras2012.interfaces

Interface Directed

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    ArcProgression, Route, Train

    public interface Directed
    Class implementing this interface signifies that the represented entity has a sense of direction, namely eastbound or westbound. The entity can never be simultaneously eastbound and westbound.

    • Method Summary

      Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      boolean isEastbound()
      Whether or not the entity is eastbound.
      boolean isWestbound()
      Whether or not the entity is westbound.

    • Method Detail

      • isEastbound

        boolean isEastbound()
        Whether or not the entity is eastbound.
        Returns:
        True if eastbound, false otherwise.

      • isWestbound

        boolean isWestbound()
        Whether or not the entity is westbound.
        Returns:
        True if westbound, false otherwise.
